Plot:

This political Thriller has its origin in a actual event, the disappearance of a young American writer and filmmaker, Charles Horman (John Shea), during a South American coup. Jack Lemmon stars as Charle's father, Ed Horman, a prominent New York businessman, who comes to the aid of Charles's wife, Betty (Sissy Spacek), in her disperate search of her missing husband. They are led in circles, up blind alleys and are confronted with lies and false hopes from both U.S. and foreing officials. But their frantically trudge on together, overcoming their past differences until the painful, shattering conclusion.


